# Task Breakdown: Configure Instagram Rate Limiting & Refactor

- [ ] Update Implementation Plan to encapsulate all cross-session context (Dynamic Scaling, Cross-App Budgets, Idempotency, Edge Cases).
- [ ] Create strict folder structure (`api/`, `rate-limiting/`, `webhook/validators/`).
- [ ] Refactor Instagram API calls to a centralized declarative tunnel (`api/client.ts` -> `fetchFromInstagram`).
- [ ] Separate validation logic from the main processing flow into isolated `validators/payload.ts`.
- [ ] Implement central error handling in the BullMQ worker processor to strip noisy try-catch blocks in the flow.
- [ ] Handle explicit edge cases centrally (Token Expired -> `isActive=false`, Spam/Privacy -> `Job Failed`, 429s -> `Delayed`, Duplicates -> `// Non fatal`).
- [ ] Implement Redis-backed limits driven by DB/API headers.
- [ ] Enforce `concurrency: 1` globally for the worker to serialize requests and read headers safely.
- [ ] Implement dynamic worker throttling based on global App-Level usage percentage reported by Redis.
- [ ] Leave a `// FIXME` for user-level idempotency checks to prevent future comment trigger spam.
- [ ] Implement clean logging with `pino.child({ jobId, instagramUserId })`.
- [ ] Test the new architecture and rate limiting logic using a mock queue script (`test-publish.ts`).
